- SCHEDULE PROGRESS UPDATE WITH COMMUNITY MONITORING ADVISORY GROUPS; AND
- GENERATE QUARTERLY EPA PROJECT PROGRESS AND FINANCIAL STATUS REPORTS.
PHASE 5 - PROJECT DATA GENERATION, DATA ANALYSIS, AND COMMUNITY COORDINATION: 
- CONTINUE VOC MEASUREMENTS AND DATA GENERATION; 
- COMPLETE AUDIT CALIBRATIONS AS REQUIRED;
- PERFORM QUALITY ANALYSIS OF DATA;
- SCHEDULE PROGRESS CLOSEOUT WITH COMMUNITY MONITORING ADVISORY GROUPS AND NEXT STEPS;
- GENERATE QUARTERLY EPA PROJECT PROGRESS AND FINANCIAL STATUS REPORTS; AND
- PREPARE FINAL EPA PROJECT CLOSEOUT REPORT

THE EXPECTED OUTCOMES INCLUDE: 
PROBLEM IDENTIFICATION - UNDERSTAND THE SPECIFIC POLLUTANTS IN THE REGION.
DEVELOP MITIGATION ACTIONS BY IDENTIFYING APPROPRIATE CONTROL STRATEGIES.
USING APPROPRIATE CONTROL STRATEGIES, REDUCE BTEX EMISSIONS.
USING APPROPRIATE CONTROL STRATEGIES, REDUCE OZONE CONCENTRATIONS.

THE INTENDED BENEFICIARIES INCLUDE  THE COMMUNITIES OF SE NEW MEXICO LOCATED WITHIN OR IN PROXIMITY TO THE PERMIAN BASIN.
